<p>The <code>bold</code> function wraps text in HTML <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> tags.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'important' | bold{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {echo 'important' | bold}</p>

<h2>Emphasize Text</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'warning' | bold{close}</pre>
<p>Warning: {echo 'warning' | bold}</p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'hello' | upper | bold{close}</pre>
<p>Loud: {echo 'hello' | upper | bold}</p>

<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | left(5) | bold{close}</pre>
<p>First word: {echo $sampleText | left(5) | bold}</p>

<pre>{open}echo 'status: ok' | after(': ') | capitalize | bold{close}</pre>
<p>Status: {echo 'status: ok' | after(': ') | capitalize | bold}</p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Outputs HTML tags directly. The text will appear bold in HTML rendering.</p>
